<HEADLINE>
<P>
'BAD GIRLS' ARE GOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re that Counterpunch on the movie "Bad Girls" (" 'Bad Girls' Fires Off Bad 
Message," May 23): Was the violence portrayed in the movie extreme? Hardly, 
when you compare this flick to that testosterone-packed film, "No Escape," or 
to the previews of Brandon Lee's last film, "The Crow." 
</P>
<P>
 It's not that I like violence in film; I don't. It's just that when you've 
spent your entire life watching women portrayed as prostitutes, victims and the 
hero's lesser half, it's refreshing to see film heroines who are capable of 
taking care of themselves. 
</P>
<P>
 MARY SHELTON 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 
</P>
</TEXT>
