<HEADLINE>
<P>
DESERT PROTECTION BILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Never before have I read anything in The Times that appalled and infuriated me 
as did the May 26 editorial, "Don't Gut Desert Protection Bill." How dare you 
advocate banning from a huge section of the eastern Mojave desert the group 
that has done more for genuine conservation and habitat preservation than all 
other such groups combined -- hunters! 
</P>
<P>
 The people you would bar from the desert are the ones who brought wildlife 
back from its condition of near-extinction at the turn of the century to its 
present state of abundance. Shame on you! The people you would ban from the 
desert are the ones who contribute nearly a billion dollars per year to such 
things as habitat enhancement projects so that our wild creatures can find a 
place to live in today's crowded world.  
</P>
<P>
 WALT SHULTZ 
</P>
<P>
 Tujunga 
</P>
