<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBERT BURLE MARX; LANDSCAPE ARCHITECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Burle Marx, 84, a world-renowned landscape architect and ecologist who 
designed more than 1,500 parks and gardens, including Rio de Janeiro's Quinta 
de Boa Vista Gardens, Flamengo Park, Copacabana Beach and Rodrigo de Freitas 
Lake.He won honors from France's Architecture Academy and London's Royal 
College of Arts. Marx studied painting and sculpture in Paris in the 1930s and 
became a self-taught biologist and world expert on Brazilian flora. Thirteen 
flower species were named after him. In 1972 he took up residence at his Santo 
Antonio da Bica Ranch outside Rio, which he transformed into an immense 
laboratory of exotic plant species from around the world. In Rio de Janeiro on 
Saturday of stomach cancer. 
</P>
