<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; THE ORIOLES' SABO ASKS TO BE TRADED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Sabo, upset at his reserve role, said he has asked to be traded by the 
Baltimore Orioles."They've made their choice, which is fine," Sabo said. 
"There's no hard feelings. . . . I did not sign here to be a reserve." Sabo has 
played little since Leo Gomez emerged as the starter at third base last month 
when Sabo was on the disabled list because of a strained back. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Colorado Rockies placed reliever Darren Holmes (0-3, 9.20 ERA) on the 
15-day disabled list because of inflammation in his right elbow. 
</P>
