<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM RUINS HULL'S DEBUT WITH THE BLADES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Anaheim Bullfrogs spoiled the debut of Blades Coach Bobby Hull Jr., 
winning, 7-1, before 8,653 at the Pond of Anaheim in the Roller Hockey 
International season opener for both teams on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Bullfrogs goalie Rob Laurie turned away 37 shots.The Blades' Brett Kurtz 
scored with 3:53 remaining in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams combined for 96 penalty minutes. Although there were three scuffles, 
only the Bullfrogs' Darren Langdon and Kurtz received 10-minute game misconduct 
penalties. 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Brown scored two second-half goals and defenseman Yuri Krivokhija had a 
goal and three assists for the Bullfrogs. 
</P>
<P>
 Colin Ward scored two first-half goals for the Bullfrogs, including one on a 
50-foot slap shot that beat Blades goalie Maxim Mihailovsky. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
