<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Pacific Symphony has been highly recommended by state arts advisers for a 
California Arts Council Challenge grant to support its commission of a 
symphonic-choral work by New York composer Elliott Goldenthal commemorating the 
Vietnam War. The panel, which met last week, gave the orchestra a 3+ ranking on 
a 1-4 scale. Typically all rankings of 3 and above receive funding. 
</P>
