<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; HOSPITAL OFFERS FREE CLASS FOR CARE GIVERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free workshop designed to help people taking care of sick patients at home 
is scheduled for June 15 at Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Called "Transitions and Change," the seminar is part of a series of workshops 
that are intended to ease the burden on care givers. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will be from 2 to 4 p.m. in Room 342 in Building 2 of the 
hospital, at 27800 Medical Center Road. 
</P>
<P>
 With advance notice, the Laguna Hills Adult Day Health Care Center will 
arrange free respite care to allow care givers to attend the seminar. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is open to people caring for family members, as well as nurses, 
social workers and other health-care professionals. 
</P>
<P>
 To register for the workshop, call (714) 283-1111. To make arrangements for 
patient care with the Laguna Hills Adult Day Health Care Center, call (714) 
855-9444. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
