WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; DRIVER ARRESTED ON THEFT, DRUG CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A United Parcel Service driver has been arrested on suspicion of stealing 
packages he was supposed to deliver for customers, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Eric Stuart, 28, of Ventura was arrested Friday by Ventura Police 
Department investigators on suspicion of grand theft, possession of drugs and 
being under the influence of drugs, a police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Stuart was arrested after he finished his shift Friday. Details were not 
available on the value of the packages and the number of thefts he is alleged 
to have committed. 
</P>
<P>
 Stuart remained in custody Sunday at the Ventura County Jail in lieu of 
$25,000 bail. He is scheduled to be arraigned Tuesday in Ventura County 
Municipal Court. J.E. MITCHELL 
