<HEADLINE>
<P>
PUBLIC INVITED TO ATTEND ECONOMIC SUMMIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County residents interested in the economic outlook of the county have 
been invited to attend the area's first economic summit Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The summit, conducted by UC Santa Barbara, will feature four speakers who will 
address the status of the local economy as well as the state and nation. 
</P>
<P>
 Scheduled speakers include Michael Carney, a professor of finance and real 
estate at Cal Poly Pomona; Larry Kimbell, director of the Business Forecasting 
Project at UCLA; Mark Schniepp, director of the Economic Forecast Project at UC 
Santa Barbara, and John Wilcox, publisher of Ventura County Newspapers. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara has held similar economic seminars in Santa Barbara and San 
Luis Obispo counties since 1981. 
</P>
<P>
 The one-day summit is sponsored by the Bank of A. Levy, the Los Angeles Times, 
the county of Ventura and Cellular One. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar at the Hyatt Westlake Plaza in Westlake will begin at 8:30 a.m. 
For more information or to register, call Hospitality Management Systems at 
684-1284. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
